    text: 'On 16 July 1054, papal legates led by Cardinal Humbert laid a bull of excommunication against Patriarch Michael Cerularius on the altar of Hagia Sophia in Constantinople; Cerularius\'s synod excommunicated the legates in turn, marking the formal East–West Schism.',
