        reason: 'Modern historians of science and folklore treat the Letter of Toledo as the archetypal medieval failed astrological prophecy — a pseudonymous, much-copied text whose specific, dated prediction was decisively refuted by events. Its emergence, spread, and falsification are documented and uncontested.',
