        occurredAt: '1240-06-12',
        datePrecision: 'DAY',
        reason: 'The disputation opens on 12 June 1240 before the royal court, with the queen mother Blanche of Castile presiding. Nicholas Donin, a Jewish convert to Christianity, lays out thirty-five accusations that the Talmud blasphemes against Christianity and Jesus; Rabbi Yehiel of Paris answers for the defence. Both a Hebrew account (the Vikuach of Rabbi Yehiel) and Latin records of the proceedings survive.',
