        reason: 'After Franco\'s death, German military archives — including the war diary of Condor Legion chief of staff Wolfram von Richthofen — and survivor and aircrew testimony confirm that the raid was a planned operation by the Condor Legion (with Italian support). Historians now uniformly attribute the destruction to the aerial bombing; the Nationalist arson story is recognised as wartime propaganda, and the German government formally apologised in 1997.',
